### India in 2026: The Statistical Snapshot
While India’s aggregate growth is enviable, its human development indicators suggest a nation at a crossroads.

| Metric (2025-26 Data) | Global Rank / Value | The Ground Reality |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **GDP (Nominal)** | 4th ($4.19 Trillion) | Surpassed Germany and the UK. |
| **GDP Per Capita** | 149th ($2,813) | Indicates extreme wealth inequality. |
| **IT Services Exports** | 1st | Global dominance in software. |
| **Press Freedom Index** | 159th | Reflects significant democratic backsliding. |
| **Air Quality** | 3rd Most Polluted | Delhi remains the world’s most polluted capital. |
| **Human Development (HDI)** | 134th | Chronic underinvestment in health and education. |

